Prac 2
1. Goto 'End Devices'

2. Select PC and Drag and drop 2 PCs into the canvas

3. Now goto 'Connections'

4. From there select 'Copper Cross-Over'

5. Click on PC1 and select 'Fast Ethernet0'

6. Now click on PC2 again select 'Fast Ethernet0'

7. Now assign IP addresses to the PCs: PC1 - 192.168.1.2
PC2 - 192.168.1.3
For this Click on PC1 and in the pop-up click on 'Desktop' - 'IP Configuration'
In IPv4 enter 192.168.1.2
Subnet Mask - 255.255.255.0
Default Gateway - 192.168.1.1
Close the pop-up
Now click on PC2 and in the pop-up click on 'Desktop' - 'IP Configuration'
In IPv4 enter 192.168.1.3
Subnet Mask - 255.255.255.0
Default Gateway - 192.168.1.1
Close the pop-up

8. To check the connectivity we use the 'ping' command

9. Click on PC1 'Command Prompt'. The command prompt of PC1 will appear. Here type the command 'ping 192.168.1.3'
(to ping PC2) If all is connected well you will get a response from PC2

10. Repeat for PC2: Click on PC2 'Command Prompt'. 
The command prompt of PC2 will appear. Here type the command 'ping 192.168.1.2' (to ping PC1) If all is connected well you will get a response from PC1
